What is the command used to sort a file ?
SORT command is used to sort a file, arranging the records in a particular order.
How will you find which operating system your system is running on  unix?
Opening terminal and then typing the command "uname -a" will display the operating system our system is running in linux.
which character you will append to a command to run the process in background?
by appending an ampersand character ( & ) to the end of the commands.
how do you see command line history in unix?
by typing History command
how do you find which process is taking how much cpu?
The vmstat command will display the information about system processes, memory, swap, I/O, and CPU performance. It will display the average details since the last reboot.

